'''Imperial Navy Troopers''', also known as '''Naval Troopers''', '''Imperial fleet troopers''', were the [[Navy|naval]] [[soldier]]s of the [[Imperial Navy]], the [[Realspace|space]] branch of the [[Galactic Empire]]'s [[Imperial Military|military]]. Those [[infantry]], who were separate from the elite, [[Color|white]]-armored [[stormtrooper]]s or the [[Imperial Army trooper|regular troopers]] of the [[Imperial Army]], were trained in advanced warfare and independent command, which included shipboard combat, repulsing boarders, and pacifying escaped [[Prisoner|detainees]]. Additionally, most were cross-trained in some operational duty. Like [[Imperial weapons technician|gunners]] and [[Imperial ground crew|ground crewmen]], Navy Troopers played a vital role in day-to-day operations.

==Description==
===Role===
[[File:Death-Star-Trooper.jpg|thumb|left|280px|The Death Star Trooper wore black uniforms and flared, reflective helmets.]]
While not as feared by [[rebel trooper]]s as their [[stormtrooper]] brethren, they still maintained an aura of importance<ref name="Rogue One Visual Guide">''[[Star Wars: Rogue One: The Ultimate Visual Guide]]''</ref> as they participated in [[Imperial Military]] assaults on installations<ref name="Twilight Company">''[[Battlefront: Twilight Company]]''</ref> and other on-the-ground operations.<ref name="Thrawn">[[Thrawn (novel)|''Thrawn'']]</ref> However, they were most commonly found guarding and maintaining far-away outposts, mining stations, and jails, and generally were not as well trained or competent.<ref name="Twilight Company" /> Although stormtroopers could serve in a similar capacity,<ref name="Vader 37">[[Darth Vader (2020) 37|''Darth Vader'' (2020) 37]]</ref> they were also found aboard Imperial starships, such as the [[Executor-class Star Dreadnought|''Executor''-class Star Dreadnought]], as a security force.<ref name="Episode V">{{Film|V}}</ref> Aboard the [[Cantwell-class Arrestor Cruiser|''Cantwell''-class Arrestor Cruiser]], Imperial Navy Troopers served in an operator role on the bridge.<ref name="Daughter of Ferrix">{{Andor|Daughter of Ferrix}}</ref>

Imperial Navy Troopers were trained to mask their emotions&mdash;such as their responses to fear, pain, surprise, and discomforts&mdash;across both their face and entire body, resulting in them standing as immobile, [[droid]]-like figures while on guard duty. The [[trooper]]s, further, were expected to take pride in the masking of their emotions.<ref name="Change of Heart">{{StoryCite|story=Change of Heart|book=From a Certain Point of View}}</ref> [[Grand Moff]] [[Wilhuff Tarkin]] himself selected a number of [[Navy]] troopers, later known as [[Death Star Trooper]]s, to set up a commanding force aboard the [[DS-1 Orbital Battle Station|Death Star]] [[battle station]]. Aboard the Death Star, those elite [[trooper]]s<ref name="SWCT_DST" />&mdash;organized under their own [[Death Star trooper officer corps|officer corps]]<ref name="Dawn">''[[Dawn of Rebellion]]''</ref>&mdash;were charged with a variety of duties for which their combat skills were not necessarily required, such as guarding detention blocks and operating the battle station's [[planet]]-killing [[superlaser]] alongside [[Imperial weapons technician]]s.<ref name="SWCT_DST" /> [[Gate officer]]s were Navy Troopers who controlled which ships could pass through the [[Shield Gate]] over [[Scarif]] to reach the [[Imperial Center of Military Research|facilities below]].<ref name="Rogue One" />

===Uniform===
[[File:Imperial-Navy-Troopers-Boarding.png|thumb|right|300px|Imperial Navy Troopers could use [[rank insignia plaque]]s to display their military ranks.]]
There were three different [[Clothing|uniforms]] worn by the troopers, although all featured the distinctive large, [[Color|black]] protective helmet with a chinstrap. The first uniform was a black [[Imperial military uniforms|Imperial officer's uniform]], sometimes complete with [[code cylinder]]s and a [[rank insignia plaque]].<ref name="Rogue One" /> The other uniforms consisted of boiler suits similar to the ones worn by Imperial technicians. Just as with technicians, they could be black<ref name="Return of the Jedi" /> or light grey.<ref name="Trouble 2">{{IDWAdventuresCite-2017|issue=5|story=The Trouble at Tibrin, Part II}}</ref> One [[Unidentified Imperial Navy Trooper (Leia Organa)|Imperial Navy Trooper]] envied the closed-face helmets of the [[Stormtrooper Corps]], reflecting how stormtroopers could hide their features, whereas Navy Troopers needed to put in the effort of masking their emotions, lest they be visible to the world. To that Navy Trooper, trying to keep one's emotions in check was the hardest part of the job.<ref name="Change of Heart" /> During the earliest period of the Empire, Navy Troopers wore a type of helmet similar to, yet still visibly distinct from,<ref name="Dark Lord 9">[[Darth Vader (2017) 9|''Darth Vader'' (2017) 9]]</ref> their finalized helmet design.<ref name="Return of the Jedi">{{Film|VI}}</ref>

==History==
===Imperial enforcers===
{{Quote|If we're expecting company, shouldn't we bring down a few more navy troopers or stormtroopers?|[[Eli N. Vanto]], to Thrawn|<ref name="Thrawn">[[Thrawn (novel)|''Thrawn'']]</ref>}}
[[File:ImperialNavyToopers-2017DarthVader9.png|thumb|left|300px|A duo of Imperial Navy Troopers pilot Darth Vader to the Jedi Temple in 19 BBY.]]
The Imperial Navy Trooper position was established in [[19 BBY]], the same year in which the Empire they served came into being.<ref name="FormationDate" /> Navy Troopers were already active shortly into the regime's existence<ref name="Dark Lord 9" /> as the [[Imperial Navy]], finding itself with increased importance, bolstered its ranks and changed up its structure, establishing the Navy Trooper position in the process.<ref name="Imperial Troops">{{EncyclopediaCite|Imperial Troops}}</ref> At that early time, Navy Troopers wore a helmet somewhat different in design<ref name="Dark Lord 9" /> to its finalized appearance.<ref name="Return of the Jedi" /> Shortly into the Imperial Era, two Navy Troopers piloted the [[Sith Lord]] [[Anakin Skywalker|Darth Vader]] aboard a [[repulsorcraft]] to the former [[Imperial Palace|Jedi Temple]], passing the [[Galaxies Opera House]] in the process, so he could [[Hunt for Jocasta Nu|confront]] surviving [[Jedi Master]] [[Jocasta Nu]] inside the Temple.<ref name="Dark Lord 9" />

Navy troopers investigated [[Mitth'raw'nuruodo]]'s [[Unidentified planet (Thrawn's exile)|planet]] early in the [[Imperial Era|era]] of the Galactic Empire, only to fall victim to Thrawn's traps before he boarded their [[Star Destroyer]], the ''[[Strikefast]]''. Upon the Imperials finding Thrawn aboard the Star Destroyer, he was brought before [[Galactic Emperor]] [[Darth Sidious|Sheev Palpatine]] on the Imperial [[capital]] world of Coruscant. Afterward, Thrawn joined the Imperial Navy and began to rise through its ranks, granting him command over detachments of navy troopers in time.<ref name="Thrawn" />

In [[13 BBY]], three navy troopers guarded the room in which Imperial Navy [[Cadet]] [[Han Solo]]'s [[Tribunal of Han Solo|tribunal]] was held. As Solo pled his case, he began approaching [[Commodore]] [[Almudin]], prompting one of the troopers to aggressively step forward. Solo stopped speaking and stepped back.<ref name="Expanded Edition">''[[Solo: A Star Wars Story: Expanded Edition]]''</ref> After Thrawn had risen through the ranks of the Imperial Navy and became an [[Admiral]], Navy Troopers served under him in the [[Batonn insurgency|Battle of Batonn]].<ref name="Thrawn" />

===Increasing war with the Rebellion===
During the [[Lothal campaign]], several navy troopers worked in Lothal's [[Galactic Empire|Imperial]] [[Imperial Complex (Lothal)|Complex's]] command center. During the final battle to liberate Lothal, former ISB agent turned Rebel Alliance Captain [[Alexsandr Kallus]] disguised himself as a trooper. The troopers then allowed Governor Pryce and the Rebels to land. When the rebels attacked, the troopers attempted to lock down the complex to no avail. The remaining navy troopers perished after Protocol 13 was initiated and the complex was destroyed.<ref name="Family Reunion – & Farewell">{{Rebels|Family Reunion &ndash; and Farewell}}</ref> A collection of elite navy troopers identified as Death Star Troopers served aboard the DS-1 Orbital Battle Station at the blessing of Grand Moff Tarking himself,<ref name="SWCT_DST" /> only for those troopers, Tarkin, and everyone else aboard the station to be killed with the Death Star's destruction during the [[Battle of Yavin]].<ref name="ANH">{{Film|IV}}</ref>

[[File:NAVYTRP.png|thumb|right|300px|Imperial Navy Troopers aboard the second Death Star]]
In [[3 ABY]],<ref name="GA">''[[Star Wars: Galactic Atlas]]''</ref> several navy troopers dragged away the lifeless body of [[Lorth Needa]] aboard the ''Executor'', after he was [[Force choke|strangled]] to death with [[the Force]] by [[Anakin Skywalker|Darth Vader]].<ref name="Episode V" /> Navy troopers also took part in the on-the-ground engagements of the [[Siege of Inyusu Tor]] against the [[61st Mobile Infantry]] on [[Sullust]]<ref name="Twilight Company">''[[Battlefront: Twilight Company]]''</ref> and the [[Battle of Endor]].<ref name="Return of the Jedi" /> In the latter, navy troopers were part of a [[Endor Imperial Navy Trooper detachment|naval trooper detachment]] operating under [[Major]] [[Hewex]].<ref name="EndorFall">{{EncyclopediaCite|The Battle of Endor and the Fall of the Empire}}</ref> Meanwhile, navy troopers served aboard the [[DS-2 Death Star II Mobile Battle Station]] as a new generation of Death Star Troopers, only for them to meet the same fate<ref name="Return of the Jedi" /> as their predecessors<ref name="ANH" /> when the Second Death Star was destroyed during the Battle of Endor.<ref name="Return of the Jedi" />

